HEADWORD: Statutable
<hw>Stat"u*ta*ble</hw> <pr>(st⟦acr⟧t"⟦usl⟧*t⟦adot⟧*b'l ; 135)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Made or introduced by statute; proceeding
from an act of the legistature; <as>as, a <ex>statutable</ex> provision
or remedy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Made or being in conformity to statute; standard;
<as>as, <ex>statutable</ex> measures</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Statutably</ent>⟦br⟧
